column13: Lifetime: The number of impressions of your Page post. (Total Count)
column14: Lifetime: The total number of people your Page post was served to. (Unique Users)
column15: Lifetime: Total number of times your video was viewed for more than 3 seconds. (Total Count)
column16: Lifetime: Number of unique people who viewed your video for more than 3 seconds. (Unique Users)
column17: Lifetime: Total number of times your video was viewed for 30 seconds or viewed to the end, whichever came first. (Total Count)
column18: Lifetime: Number of unique people who viewed your video for 30 seconds or to the end, whichever came first. (Unique Users)
column19: Lifetime: The number of times your video was watched at 95% of its length , including watches that skipped to this point. (Total Count)
column20: Lifetime: The number of unique people who watched your video at 95% of its length, including people that skipped to this point. (Unique Users)
column21: Lifetime: The number of people who viewed your video for at least 60 seconds, given that the video is at least 60 seconds long. (Total Count)
column22: Lifetime: The number of unique people who viewed your video for at least 60 seconds, given that the video is at least 60 seconds long. (Unique Users)
column23: Lifetime: Number of times your video started automatically playing and people viewed it for more than 3 seconds. (Total Count)
column24: Lifetime: Number of times people clicked to play your video and viewed it more than 3 seconds. (Total Count)
column25: Lifetime: Number of times your video started automatically playing and people viewed it for 30 seconds or to the end, whichever came first. (Total Count)
column26: Lifetime: Number of times people clicked to play your video and viewed it for 30 seconds or to the end, whichever came first. (Total Count)
column27: Lifetime: Number of times your video started automatically playing and people watched it at 95% of its length, including watches that skipped to this point. (Total Count)
column28: Lifetime: Number of times people clicked to play your video and watched it at 95% of its length, including watches that skipped to this point. (Total Count)
column29: Lifetime: The number of impressions of your Page post in an Ad or Sponsored Story. (Total Count)
column30: Lifetime: The number of impressions of your post in News Feed or ticker or on your Page's Timeline. (Total Count)
column31: Lifetime: Number of times your video was viewed more than 3 seconds after paid promotion. (Total Count)
column32: Lifetime: Number of times your video was viewed for more than 3 seconds without any paid promotion. (Total Count)
column33: Lifetime: Number of times your video was viewed for 30 seconds or viewed to the end, whichever came first, after a paid promotion. (Total Count)
column34: Lifetime: Number of times your video was viewed for 30 seconds or viewed to the end, whichever came first, without a paid promotion. (Total Count)
column35: Lifetime: The number of times your video was watched at 95% of its length after paid promotion, including watches that skipped to this point. (Total Count)
column36: Lifetime: The number of times your video was watched at 95% of its length without any paid promotion, including watches that skipped to this point. (Total Count)
column37: Lifetime: Views of your video at each interval as a percentage of all views. This metric doesn't count views of videos while they were live. Retention graphs may show more viewers later in the video than at the beginning. People might start the video in the middle, skip ahead, save and rewatch it from that point, or other similar behaviors. (Total Count)
column78: Lifetime: Auto-played views of your video at each interval as a percentage of all auto-played views. This metric does not count views of videos while they were live. Retention graphs may show more viewers later in the video than at the beginning. People might start the video in the middle, skip ahead, save and rewatch it from that point, or other similar behaviors. (Total Count)
column119: Lifetime: Clicked-to-play views of your video at each interval as a percentage of all clicked-to-play views. This metric does not count views of videos while they were live. Retention graphs may show more viewers later in the video than at the beginning. People might start the video in the middle, skip ahead, save and rewatch it from that point, or other similar behaviors. (Total Count)
column160: Lifetime: The number of clicks anywhere in your post, by type. (Total Count)
column164: Lifetime: The number of people who clicked anywhere in your post, by type. (Unique Users)
column168: Lifetime: The number of stories created about your Page post, by action type. (Total Count)
column171: Lifetime: The number of unique people who created a story about your Page post by interacting with it. (Unique Users)

column3: OTV - Open Television shared an episode of Comedy Central Originals.

Our #wcw goes out to Arnetta Randall, the creator of Hook-Ups, a new comedic web series that explores modern dating practices among black people from many backgrounds, gender expressions, and sexual orientations. 

See Hook-Ups June 8th at Open Television Premieres: New Black TV at Dorchester Art + Housing Collaborative | Rebuild Foundation.

Our #mcm goes out to Vincent Rodriguez III of Crazy Ex-Girlfriend with a reminder that it's not enough to just be "aware" of Asian-Americans. 

#AsianPacficAmericanHeritageMonth

You Should Know This By Now is directed by Reena Dutt, produced by Archana M Jain & Fawzia Mirza, and written by Fawzia Mirza and Reena Dutt with some improv from the cast.

Black queers date and fall in lust. 

Hook Ups premieres this summer, stay tuned.

Did you know May is #nationalmasturbationmonth ? Get in the mood with the "Fingers" episode of F*ck Yes Series, starring Marnie Alton & Erica C. Anderson, written by Julie Keck and Jessica King of King is a Fink Productions directed by Emily Best. Season two is now available on weareo.tv! This adult sex ed series shows that consent isn't only mandatory, it can be very sexy.

You can watch season one on Seed&Spark: https://www.seedandspark.com/watch/fck-yes

The Middle East isn't a continent y'all. C'mon. 

Your Friday pearl of wisdom brought to you by Muslim Iranian-American comedian, Zahra Noorbakhsh. 

#AsianPacificAmericanHeritageMonth #femalefilmmakerfriday

In honor of Asian Pacific American Heritage Month, a series of Public Service Announcements (PSAs) from artists within our communities. Inspired by ‘The More You Know’ campaign, the current administration and Asians who think this is stuff you should know by now. Watch the others right here: https://vimeo.com/channels/1362984

Directed by Reena Dutt
Produced by Archana M Jain & Fawzia Mirza
Written by Fawzia Mirza 
Additional Writing by Reena Dutt & some awesome improv by the cast!
Director of Photography Lisa Tom
Edited by Ryan Logan
Location Sound Daniel Trujillo
Graphics Jake Myers
Original Theme Song @Timo Chen 
PAs Sreejith Nair & Mayuri Bhandari
Special Thanks: Mimi, Michelle, Roshan, Nabeela

Miss us? On June 8th we will premiering an array of brilliant new works at Rebuild Foundation. One of the pieces is "Darling Shear", a docu-series by Diana Quinones Rivera that follows choreographer Darling Shear and her group of dancers: AaLiyah ChrisTina, Alix Schillaci, Andy Slavin, Rashida KhanBey-Miller, and Tila Von Twirl, as they explore their personal understandings of identity, expression, movement, and collaboration.

RSVP and find more information here: Open Television Premieres: New Black TV

In honor of #AsianPacificAmericanHeritageMonth we're dropping some knowledge. 

Enjoy "You Should Know This By Now", a series of comedic PSAs from artists within our communities. Inspired by ‘The More You Know’ campaign, the current administration and Asians who think this is stuff you should know by now. Concept by Fawzia Mirza. 

Watch the full series here: https://vimeo.com/channels/1362984/. Other artists in the series include Vincent Rodriguez III of Crazy Ex-Girlfriend, Zahra Noorbakhsh of the #GoodMuslimBadMuslim podcast, comedian @Atsuko Okatsuka Comedian/Actress and many more!
